sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant UI as Extension UI (browser)
    participant SW as Extension Service Worker
    participant SF as Customer Salesforce Org
    participant API as Jetstream Server

    Note over U,API: The extension runs on a Salesforce tab where the user is already logged in.

    rect rgb(232, 240, 254)
    Note over U,SF: Salesforce data path - 100% browser <-> Salesforce (DIRECT)
    U->>UI: Run query / action
    UI->>UI: axios adapter intercepts /api/* locally (no network to Jetstream)
    UI->>SW: GET_CURRENT_ORG / GET_SESSION
    SW->>SW: Read Salesforce "sid" session cookie from browser cookie store
    SW-->>UI: { sessionToken = sid, instanceUrl }
    UI->>UI: Build ApiConnection (Bearer = sid cookie)
    UI->>SF: HTTPS {instanceUrl}/services/data/... (Bearer sid)
    SF-->>UI: Salesforce records
    Note over UI,SF: Runs the SAME salesforce-api client as the web app,<br/>but the fetch originates in the browser, straight to Salesforce.
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
    Note over SW,API: Jetstream server - control plane only (NO Salesforce data)
    SW->>API: /web-extension/auth/verify (JWT) - account entitlement
    opt If user enables record-history sync
        UI->>API: /web-extension/data-sync (saved queries / history metadata)
    end
    end

    Note over U,API: Salesforce record data and the Salesforce session token<br/>NEVER traverse Jetstream servers.
